            "abstract": [
                {
                    "p": "The invention discloses a low-carbon ironmaking method and system. The method comprises the steps that iron ore is subjected to a pre-reduction reaction in a pre-reduction furnace, and a metallization product and first coal gas are generated; the metallization product is subjected to a deep reduction reaction in a deep reduction furnace, and molten iron, slag and second coal gas are generated; the first coal gas and the second coal gas are subjected to grid connection, drying, dust removal, decarburization and heating to obtain high-temperature reducing gas with the temperature higher than 800 DEG C, and the high-temperature reducing gas and hydrogen-rich or pure hydrogen gas with the temperature lower than 800 DEG C serve as reducing agents of the pre-reduction reaction. The technical problem that hydrogen-rich or pure hydrogen gas is heated to a high temperature and the problem of hydrogen embrittlement of equipment can be avoided."
                },
                {
                    "p": "本发明公开了一种低碳炼铁方法及系统。所述方法包括：使得铁矿石在预还原炉内进行预还原反应，生成金属化产物和第一煤气；使得所述金属化产物在深度还原炉内进行深度还原反应，生成铁水、炉渣和第二煤气；对所述第一煤气和所述第二煤气进行并网、干燥、除尘、脱碳、加热，以获得温度高于800℃的高温还原气，并使得所述高温还原气和温度低于800℃的富氢或纯氢气体作为所述预还原反应的还原剂。本发明能够避免将富氢或纯氢气体加热到高温的技术难题以及设备氢脆问题。"
                }
            ]
